Prominent city lawyer John Juma had a colourful wedding last Saturday. Juma tied the knot to Nancy Omiti at Safari Park Hotel. They have been together for the last 15 years. Present were their two sons Fidel Juma and Trevor Akide and daughter Kendra Milan. “This is finally the culmination of my dream to marry the love of my life,” the bride Nancy Omiti told the Star. Guests included Devolution CS Eugene Wamalwa, Law Society of Kenya vice president Harriette Chiggai and Nairobi lawyer Ashitiva Mandale. Juma is a practising advocate, certified public secretary and trustee at Lap Trust, representing LSK.